Gradle is a build tool with a focus on build automation and support for multi-language development. If you are building, testing, publishing, and deploying software on any platform, Gradle offers a flexible model that can- **User App List**: View and search all user-installed applications.
- **Risk Filtering**: Quickly filter apps by **Unreliable** (high-risk) or **Reliable** (low-risk) status.
- **Detailed Inspection**: Deep-dive into each app's permissions.
- **Classification Sections**: Permissions are clearly separated into **Unreliable** and **Reliable** groups.
- **Direct Navigation**: Clicking the **Reliable** button on an app card takes you straight to its detailed overview.
lopment tools and continuous integration servers including Eclipse, IntelliJ, and Jenkins.

For more information about Gradle, please visit: https://gradle.org

If you are using the "all" distribution, the User Manual is included in your distribution.

If you are using the "bin" distribution, a copy of the User Manual is available on https://docs.gradle.org.

Typing `gradle help` prints the command line help.

Typing `gradle tasks` shows all the tasks of a Gradle build.
